Azure.ResourceManager.AppService 1.4.1

### Describe the bug

I have a Web App with a managed identity that has only the contributor role on the App Service Plan it runs on.

I need to be able to update the SKU directly on the resource :

```csharp
var client = new ArmClient(new DefaultAzureCredential());

var aspResource = AppServicePlanResource.CreateResourceIdentifier(subscriptionId, resourceGroupName, aspName);
var asp = await aspResource.GetAsync();

var patch = new AppServicePlanPatch()
{
    WorkerTierName = "P5mv3",
};

await asp.Value.UpdateAsync(patch);
```

Other workarounds like https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/issues/32517#issuecomment-1346373852 are not an option since it requires more privileges.

### Expected behavior

The following code is supposed to update the App Service Plan Pricing tier

### Actual behavior

It returns an HTTP400

```json
{
  "Code": "BadRequest",
  "Message": "The parameter SKU cannot be null.",
  "Target": null,
  "Details": [
    {
      "Message": "The parameter SKU cannot be null."
    },
    {
      "Code": "BadRequest"
    },
    {
      "ErrorEntity": {
        "MessageTemplate": "The parameter {0} cannot be null.",
        "Parameters": [
          "SKU"
        ],
        "Code": "BadRequest",
        "Message": "The parameter SKU cannot be null."
      }
    }
  ],
  "Innererror": null
}
```

### Reproduction Steps

Create an app service plan get the resource id and try to update it with the code snippet above

